|accessdate=2006-10-23}}</ref>
and Beverly Palmer<ref name="bloodfound">{{cite news
|author=Harris, Harry
|coauthors=Dearen, Jason
|title=Missing woman's blood found in husband's house
|publisher=[[San Jose Mercury News]]
|date=October 11, 2006
|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/mld/mercurynews/news/15735159.htm|accessdate=2006-10-11
|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20070127232217/http://www.mercurynews.com/mld/mercurynews/news/15735159.htm|archivedate = 2007-01-27}}</ref> on December 19, 1963. He grew up in [[California]] and dropped out of [[junior high school]] before he was 14. He was accepted at the [[University of California, Berkeley]], at the age of 15, which he attended off and on until he received a [[Bachelor of Arts|BA]] in [[computer-science]] in 1992, aged 28.<ref name="sfgate20061010">{{cite news
|author=Lee, Henry K.
|title=Husband of missing Oakland mom arrested on suspicion of murder
